# Architecture rules -> Next.js App Router + shadcn/ui

Reference document: `architecture.md` (root of repo).
These rules are derived from it. When a rule here and `architecture.md` conflict, `architecture.md` wins -> update this file to match.

---

## Layer boundaries (enforced on every file)

### `app/` -> routing only
- `page.tsx` and `layout.tsx` files must contain at most: imports, one exported default function, one JSX return that renders a single feature component.
- No data fetching, no hooks, no business logic, no multi-component JSX.

```tsx
// CORRECT
import { SettingsPage } from '@/components/features/settings/SettingsPage'
export default function Page() { return <SettingsPage /> }

// WRONG -> data fetch in route file
export default async function Page() {
  const user = await getUser() // ❌ move this into SettingsPage
  return <Settings user={user} />
}
```

### `server/queries/` -> reads
- First line after imports: `import 'server-only'`
- Every exported function is wrapped with `cache()` from `'react'`
- Returns typed value or `null` / `[]` -> never throws for empty data
- No mutations, no `revalidatePath`, no side effects

### `server/actions/` -> writes
- First line of file: `'use server'`
- Structure: auth check → Zod validation → DB mutation → revalidate → return `ActionResult<T>`
- Always returns `ActionResult<T>` -> never `void`, never throws to caller
- Never imported at the module level of a `'use client'` file

### `components/ui/` -> untouchable
- Zero edits. Zero. Add via `npx shadcn@latest add`.
- Extend in `components/shared/` instead.

---

## `'use client'` placement

Push `'use client'` as deep as possible:

```
page.tsx (RSC)
└── FeaturePage.tsx (RSC -> fetches data)
    ├── StaticSection.tsx (RSC)
    └── InteractiveForm.tsx ('use client' ← only here)
```

Do not mark a component `'use client'` unless it uses:
- `useState`, `useReducer`, `useRef`, `useEffect`
- Browser APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`)
- Event handlers that need closure over local state
- Third-party hooks that require client context

---

## TypeScript

Always derive from Zod -> never duplicate:

```ts
// types/schemas/post.ts
export const postSchema = z.object({ title: z.string().min(1), body: z.string() })
export type Post      = z.infer<typeof postSchema>        // ✅
export type PostInput = z.infer<typeof postSchema.partial()> // ✅

// WRONG -> hand-written type that duplicates schema
export type Post = { title: string; body: string } // ❌
```

Return type must be annotated on every exported async function:

```ts
// ✅
export async function getUser(id: string): Promise<User | null> { ... }

// ❌
export async function getUser(id: string) { ... }
```

